  "title": "Widget proposal: numericRefinementList",
  "body": "Following #295. Here a first draft of api proposal\n# API\n\n```\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.numericRefinementList({\n    container: '#refinement-date-selector',\n    attributeName: 'age'\n    options: [\n      {name: 'All'},\n      {end: 4, name: 'less than 4'},\n      {start: 4, end: 4, name: '4'},\n      {start: 5, end: 10, name: 'between 5 and 9'},\n      {start: 11, name: 'more than 10'},\n    ]\n    // cssClasses: {root, header, body, footer, list, item, active, label, checkbox, count}\n    // templates: {header, item, footer}\n    // label: \"Age\"\n    // hideContainerWhenNoRefinements: true\n    // options.operator='or'\n  })\n);\n```\n\nThe rendering would be the same as refinement list the thing that will change is how we handle the refiements\n\nI did an example with age but this widget would be able to be use for date and handle things like:\n\n![](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/976175/10609358/972d2a06-7743-11e5-94e8-0700731f7564.png)\n",
